Capital League 2

Placings 1983 to 2016 (34 seasons)

 

This league is at Tier 3 in the Brisbane football system and has been below the Brisbane Premier League and the Tier 2 league (currently Capital League 1) since 1983.

 

This league has been known as:

  • Division 2 (1983)
  • Division 1 (1984-1986)
  • Division 3 (1987-1996)
  • Amateur Division 1 (1997 to 2001)
  • Division 2 (2002)
  • Premier Division 2 (2003-2012)
  • Capital League 2 (since 2013)

 

The placings below in two tables are based on Brisbane Tier 3 standings at the end of the regular season, prior to the final series:

ยง         1. Season by season 1983 to 2002

ยง         2. Season by season 2003 to 2016

ยง         3. Ranking of clubs
